features: AMD Socket AM5(LGA 1718): Ready for AMD Ryzen 7000 Series desktop processors
Robust Power Solution: 12 + 2 power stages with 8 + 4 pin ProCool power connectors, high-quality alloy chokes, and durable capacitors to support multi-core processors
Optimized Thermal Design: Massive VRM heatsinks with strategically cut airflow channels and high conductivity thermal pads
Next-Gen M.2 Support: One PCIe 5.0 M.2 slot and two PCIe 4.0 M.2 slots, all with heatsinks to maximize performance
Advanced Connectivity: One USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C and ten additional rear USB ports, USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type-C front-panel connector, HDMI 2.1, DisplayPort 1.4, and one PCIe 5.0 x16 SafeSlot
High-Performance Networking: On-board WiFi 6E (802.11ax), Bluetooth 5.2, and Intel 2.5G Ethernet with ASUS LANGuard
Intelligent Control: ASUS-exclusive Two-Way AI Noise Cancelation and AI Networking
Unmatched Personalization: ASUS-exclusive Aura Sync RGB lighting, including one RGB header and three addressable Gen 2 RGB headers
DIY-Friendly Design: PCIe Slot Q-release, M.2 Q-Latch, Pre-mounted I/O shield, and BIOS FlashBack button
Intuitive Software: Easy-to-use UEFI BIOS dashboard, Armoury Crate RGB and device manager, and bundled 60-day AIDA64 Extreme trial
body.description: ASUS ROG STRIX B650E-F GAMING WIFI motherboard is built for gamers who pursue optimal in-game experience with boosted power delivery and an optimized cooling design to maximize the demand for Ryzen 7000 series processors. Along with the latest Wi-Fi 6E, DDR5 Memory, and PCI Express® 5.0 for superfast data transfer, memory, and storage performance, ROG STRIX B650E-F GAMING WiFi is unmistakably ROG with its futuristic design elements, iridescent ROG logo, monochrome finish and Aura lighting that will give your build a subtle but vibrant look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great motherboard - works perfectly
reviews.reviewText: I was a bit apprehensive about this MB based on some of the mixed reviews on Amazon, but I’m happy to report that it is working just fine, and I did not need to flash the BIOS.I had some trouble at first when my system wouldn’t post. The DRAM LED was illuminated, so I just powered down the system, reseated my RAM cards, and started back up. The system posted without a problem after that. The only other hiccup I ran into was I needed to install the WiFi driver before to get WiFi up and running. This is kinda silly, as it requires you to have another computer to download the drivers (either LAN or WiFi) in order to get connectivity. Nothing that a Chromebook and thumb drive can’t fix, but it still just seems silly. ASUS should just include those drivers out of the box.I’m running an AMD Ryzen 7 7800X3D, ASUS TUF 4070Ti, and 32BG of G.Skill Trident Z5 Neo RGB DDR5 RAM on Windows 11. The system works great, and I’m very happy with this motherboard purchase.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Motherboard in Price Range
reviews.reviewText: Built my pc amount a month ago. This is the motherboard I used. This has worked perfectly since I installed it with no issues at all. It has PCIE 5.0 GPU slot so it allows for some future proofing as it is ready for next gen PCIE 5.0 GPU's for whenever those release. I had no compatibility issues with any of my parts. I also have an extremely large Air cooling CPU cooler, and it fits with good clearance. Another plus is this motherboard comes with WIFI and Bluetooth, both of which have worked great for me.For reference, this is the build I am using it for;Motherboard: ASUS ROG Strix B650E-F Gaming WiFi AM5GPU: GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 4070 Eagle OC 12G Graphics CardCPU: AMD Ryzen 7 7800X3D 8-Core, 16-ThreadRAM: CORSAIR VENGEANCE RGB DDR5 RAM 32GB (2x16GB) 6000MHzSSD: WD_BLACK 1TB SN850X NVMe Internal Gaming SSD Solid State Drive - Gen4 PCIe, M.2 2280, Up to 7,300 MB/sPower Supply: Corsair RM1000x Shift Fully Modular ATX Power SupplyCPU Cooler: be quiet! reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars First build went better than expected!
reviews.reviewText: Pros / ConsPros - Bios menu is well built and easy to understand (there is advanced settings/menu for more experienced users), supports EXPO (make sure you enable it if you need), 3 m.2 slots, plenty SATA connections, RGBs, low temps, fast wifi, fan control in bios (easy to tweak fan speeds and compare noise levels), bios flashback is a nice feature (can update bios with or without cpu), no blue screens to date!Cons - VERY slow startup/boot, no wifi out of box (will need to download via USB), BIOS may require an update before it displays the correct ram speed. Some tight fits (to gain access to one of the m.2 slots you have to remove the GPU, ATX power connection location is TIGHT)*Important note* The previous MB I got from ASUS arrived damaged. The customer service rep at ASUS was terrible and told me I'd have to pay an initial investigation fee of $30 plus shipping and whatever else is needed. Really terrible service but Amazon was awesome and gave me a refund so and I ended up purchasing this MB.Tldr; It's a solid 7.5/10. Not the best, some slight hiccups here and there but does the job. I'm happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars DOA, paid 115 for repair, and STILL DOA
reviews.reviewText: I paid 1700+ on parts for a new computer, I heard that ASUS was a trusted brand, so I decided to buy an ASUS Motherboard. Bad idea, I look at all the manuals, and make sure I'm doing things correctly, by the book. Everything went all right until we got to booting it up, The Motherboard lights turned on, as well as the DRAM light, but no other LEDs, which are important. I try to troubleshoot it by moving wires around. still doesn't work. I then read online how to do a BIOS flash, which is testing to see if it was the motherboard that was bad and not the CPU, still not booting. All this while I was contacting support, looking for any solution, they then asked for us to ship it in for a diagnostic, which we had to not only pay for shipping but also pin damage we didn't see before we shipped it. After 2 weeks and 115 dollars, the board returns, I put it back together again and it goes quicker and smoother than the first time. STILL the same issue, with no boot, but at least motherboard lights, DRAM light, and 1/3 of fans are working. I'm now sending this board back, no visible damage, at least not done by me. I'm sending this motherboard back, hoping to get a full refund, and I'm going to buy a different brand.Not recommended since I'm seeing the same issue with this board amongst the other 1-star reviews.

reviews.reviewTitle: Perfect for mid range motherboards, but...
reviews.reviewText: This motherboard is really good if you are looking to build a PC for gaming and maybe some hobby stuff like video editing.HOWEVER, one major thing you must consider before buying this motherboard is -The bottom most PCIE slot and the Nvme slot SHARE THE SAME MOTHERBOARD CHIPSET EXPRESSLANE.Meaning: you can either use only one of the slots NOT BOTH.Consider this before buying.What problems can you face with this?Not much really.Lemme give you an example.Me personally, I am using the PCIE slot for a video capture card and I don't plan on using the Nvme slot.So if you are a gamer that wants all the storage and maybe wants to stream, this motherboard cannot offer both unless you decide to use another PC for streaming.It's either use the Nvme slot for storage or use the PCIE slot for other devices.Other than that, this motherboard is beautiful.

Beautiful board. Expo and xmp profiles work great. Ryzen Master sucks with this, but whatever. The small bells and whistles vs. my last board, which was in the same league and level but AM4, are neat. Would recommend.
